===Noun===
the '''six perfections'''
#In [[Mahayana]] [[Buddhism]], the six virtues which the [[bodhisattva]] must practice in their avowed pursuit of bringing all beings to [[enlightenment]] through [[bodhicitta]]; they are [[dana]] (munificence), [[sila]] (ethicality), [[ksanti]] (patience), [[virya]] (determination), [[dhyana]] (meditation), and [[prajna]] (wisdom).

